Class ReceivedMessageEvent

java.lang.Object
  OpenFlow.NBAPI.ReceivedMessageEvent
Direct Known Subclasses:
ReceivedMessageEventMarker
public class ReceivedMessageEvent
extends java.lang.Object

Call-back data associated with a received message.

A ReceivedMessageEvent object contains call-back data associated with a received SBOFMessagePB message from the switch (via the controller). The event is populated by immutable instance members. For messages of OFTypePB.PACKET_IN, the filter member is the filter that selected the packet for the call-back, whereas the packet_data member is the set of filter fields populated from the packet data.

The app_map member allows for various call-backs to coordinate processing. Any Thread object stored as a value in the map will be started when dispatch is complete. However, such threads should be added through implemntation of the ReceivedMessageCallPrep interface, as the prep calls are guaranteed to have been made before dispatch is complete (execution of the call-backs are done in one or more separate threads to prevent blocking the main reader thread).
